The <b>Rufous Piha</b> (<i>Lipaugus unirufus</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cotingidae" title="Cotingidae" class="mw-redirect">Cotingidae</a> family. It is found in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belize" title="Belize">Belize</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title="Colombia">Colombia</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Costa_Rica" title="Costa Rica">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecuador" title="Ecuador">Ecuador</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guatemala" title="Guatemala">Guatemala</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduras" title="Honduras">Honduras</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicaragua" title="Nicaragua">Nicaragua</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Panama" title="Panama">Panama</a>.
Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitat</a> is subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a>.
